column3: “intense head high, great for walking and working.”

“Super heady sativa. Racy feeling strain. Seeds from PeakSeedsBC grown outdoors was fantastic.
Taste is chemically sweet. Joints smoke from sweet on a dry hit eventually turning sweet and sour towards the end.
Frisbee weed for sure.”

“Crazy head high will hit like a train at times. Will have you planted in the chair but not so much your useless. Amazing sweet citrus smell of the bud the smoke flavour i notice tends to be a sweet earthy taste to me would recommend!!!!”
“great strain for flavour and high no paranoia what so ever and easy to grow , great beguinner strain.”
“I love it.... it's a mind and body tingling feeling definitely feel the sativa energy. My wake and bake is on point today”
“this strain is perfect for cluster headaches!”
“This listing is invalid. The cross between SK1 and NL5 is called Shiva Skunk. It first won the Cannabis Cup in 1997.”

“Purchased it from Unified collective, large buds but was very dry, it also had many large stems. Within a few days the buds began to basically resemble shake. Also, doesn't get you too high (coming from a regular smoker). To top it off, this dispensary had a cheaper ounce (Fast Eddi) which was superior to Sweet skunk.”
